msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:268
msgid ""
"These guidelines establish the technical and social conventions that "
"determine interactions between developers, and between developers and "
"users.  They apply to all developers, both those hired by the City Council "
"and external developers, as well as Council staff."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:270
msgid ""
"They must be drawn up in English and either be a GitHub/Gitlab wiki page or "
"a text file with light markup language."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:272
msgid ""
"The guidelines might grow over time but, initially, only three things need "
"to be made clear:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:274
msgid "What communication channels the project has and what each one is used for."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:275
msgid ""
"Instructions on how to report bugs and how to make contributions to the "
"project."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:276
msgid "A brief description of project governance: who takes decisions and how."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:280
msgid ""
"In many cases the only thing that needs to be said about the third point is "
"that while the contract is in force, the City Council will prioritise the "
"features to be developed and the bugs to be sorted out.  The Council also "
"has the last word on the technical solutions to be adopted, the "
"contributions to be integrated and the versions to be published.  It might "
"also be mentioned that in the future an appropriate governance model will be "
"studied for the project’s changing circumstances."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:282
msgid "These Developer Guidelines should, as a minimum, be linked from:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:284 modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:375
msgid "The `README` file of the main repository."
msgstr ""

#. type: Block title
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "Publish detailed Developer Guidelines (if the project grows)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: modules/ROOT/pages/communities.adoc:297
msgid ""
"For big projects, and without it being the first measure to adopt, it could "
"be useful to work on and publish some broader, more detailed Developer "
"Guidelines than those proposed in the "
"link:#publicar-breus-directrius-desenvolupadors[Measure: (Day 1) Publish "
"brief Developer Guidelines]."
msgstr ""

